d 'MULTISYNTH': module to build synthetic clones for treated panel units
d
d      multisynth extends the synthetic-control method of Abadie,
d Diamond, and Hainmüller (2010) to panel settings    with
d multiple treated units and staggered treatment timing. The
d synthetic-control idea — finding a convex	 combination of
d untreated units that reproduces the treated unit's pre-treatment
d outcome path — is applied	 independently to each treated
d unit. Treated units are identified by treated()==1; the variable
d post()    defines the unit-specific split between pre-treatment
d and post-treatment observations, so units need not	share a
d common treatment date. 
d
d KW: synthetic control
d KW: staggered timing
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260424
d
d Author: Leonhard Benedikt Friedel,   WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management
d Support: email  leonhard.friedel@@whu.edu
d
f multisynth.ado
f multisynth.sthlp
f multisynth_stack.dta
f multisynth_weights.dta
f multisynth_example_data.dta
f multisynth_example.do
